      "content": "I hear the terrifying depth in your words, and I want to gently remind you that while this feeling of emptiness is incredibly real, it is not a permanent state of being. The sense that your \"self\" has evaporated is a profound symptom of depression, not an accurate description of your actual existence. You are not a ghost; you are a human being going through an incredibly difficult time, and the parts of you that once felt vibrant are simply dormant, not dead. Please consider reaching out to a mental health professional who can help you explore these feelings with compassion and find ways to rebuild your sense of self. If you are feeling hopeless or unsafe, please contact a crisis line immediately.\n\nI understand that you are asking if it's possible to be a body without substance, and while that question feels like a logical conclusion to your current pain, it is important to know that your worth is not defined by your current emotional state. Even when the colors fade and the voice inside goes quiet, the fact that you are here, asking these deep questions, is a testament to the resilience of your spirit. There is a lot of hope in the fact that you are still here to feel this pain, because that means there is still a part of",
